data.title: An Ambition Reduced to Ashes
data.meta_description: An Ambition Reduced to Ashes  is a 1995 Cambodian short feature drama film written and directed by Norodom Sihanouk, King of Cambodia. The film was made right after his recovery from cancer in Beijing, China.
data.text: An Ambition Reduced to Ashes is a 1995 Cambodian short feature drama film written and directed by Norodom Sihanouk, King of Cambodia. The film was made right after his recovery from cancer in Beijing, China.[2]
